 template can access a class. It seems I need an object with a method that returns Runtime, and I wonder if static models would help here. The Legacy policy blocks dangerous methods only through the introspector. So, could I configure the BeansWrapper with `LegacyDefaultMemberAccessPolicy` to expose a Class object? I’ll need to verify if templates can access methods. For simplification, maybe using `BeansWrapper wrapper = new BeansWrapper(Configuration.VERSION_2_3_21)` would work and would be legacy by default, but I think the default might change for versions below 2.3.30.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_Tw3SqgK4ePTWTYqy6xd8GOVM|fc_05a814cff32de2870169f4af41d99481968f5fceac7a2f13c8", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "../../source_context/org.freemarker/freemarker/2.3.31/main/extracted/freemarker/ext/beans/DefaultMemberAccessPolicy.java", "limit": 110}, "partialJson": "{\"path\":\"../../source_context/org.freemarker/freemarker/2.3.31/main/extracted/freemarker/ext/beans/DefaultMemberAccessPolicy.java\",\"limit\":110}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1600, "output": 569, "cacheRead": 34304, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 36473, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777643317682, "responseId": "resp_05a814cff32de2870169f4af3617b48196a833d37083f1f141"}}
